verses.text: Truly God \add is\add* good to Israel , \add even\add* to such as are of a clean heart.\f + \fr 73.1 \ft of: or, for\f*\f + \fr 73.1 \ft Truly: or, Yet\f*\f + \fr 73.1 \ft of…: Heb. clean of heart\f* \q1
But as for me, my feet were almost gone ; my steps had well nigh slipped. \q1
For I was envious at the foolish , \add when\add* I saw the prosperity of the wicked. \q1
For \add there are\add* no bands in their death : but their strength \add is\add* firm.\f + \fr 73.4 \ft firm: Heb. fat\f* \q1

They \add are\add* not in trouble \add as other\add* men ; neither are they plagued like \add other\add* men.\f + \fr 73.5 \ft in…: Heb. in the trouble of other men\f*\f + \fr 73.5 \ft like: Heb. with\f* \q1
Therefore pride compasseth them about as a chain ; violence covereth them \add as\add* a garment. \q1
Their eyes stand out with fatness : they have more than heart could wish.\f + \fr 73.7 \ft have…: Heb. pass the thoughts of the heart\f* \q1
They are corrupt , and speak wickedly \add concerning\add* oppression : they speak loftily. \q1
They set their mouth against the heavens , and their tongue walketh through the earth. \q1
Therefore his people return hither : and waters of a full \add cup\add* are wrung out to them. \q1
And they say , How doth God know ? and is there knowledge in the most High ? \q1
Behold, these \add are\add* the ungodly , who prosper in the world ; they increase \add in\add* riches. \q1
Verily I have cleansed my heart \add in\add* vain , and washed my hands in innocency. \q1
For all the day long have I been plagued , and chastened every morning.\f + \fr 73.14 \ft chastened: Heb. my chastisement was\f* \b \q1
If I say , I will speak thus ; behold, I should offend \add against\add* the generation of thy children. \q1
When I thought to know this, it \add was\add* too painful for me ;\f + \fr 73.16 \ft too…: Heb. labour in mine eyes\f* \q1
Until I went into the sanctuary of God ; \add then\add* understood I their end. \q1
Surely thou didst set them in slippery places : thou castedst them down into destruction. \q1
How are they \add brought\add* into desolation , as in a moment ! they are utterly consumed with terrors. \q1
As a dream when \add one\add* awaketh ; \add so\add*, O Lord , when thou awakest , thou shalt despise their image. \b \q1
Thus my heart was grieved , and I was pricked in my reins. \q1
So foolish \add was\add* I, and ignorant : I was \add as\add* a beast before thee.\f + \fr 73.22 \ft ignorant: Heb. I knew not\f*\f + \fr 73.22 \ft before: Heb. with\f* \q1
Nevertheless I \add am\add* continually with thee: thou hast holden \add me\add* by my right hand. \q1
Thou shalt guide me with thy counsel , and afterward receive me \add to\add* glory. \q1
Whom have I in heaven \add but thee\add*? and \add there is\add* none upon earth \add that\add* I desire beside thee. \q1
My flesh and my heart faileth : \add but\add* God \add is\add* the strength of my heart , and my portion for ever.\f + \fr 73.26 \ft strength: Heb. rock\f* \q1
For, lo, they that are far from thee shall perish : thou hast destroyed all them that go a whoring from thee. \q1
But \add it is\add* good for me to draw near to God : I have put my trust in the Lord \nd \+w GOD|strong="H3069"\+w*\nd*, that I may declare all thy works.
